Text: RE duck hookKeith i would love to meet you for a beer but i am in massachusetts at the moment hopefully this headhunter chick can set me up with some interviews in houston and we can meet up then As for your world tour it really depends on how much you want to see You can take months and rush through countries and just see their main tourist sights or you can take the same months and see countries really thouroughly and get a feel for a pleaces people culture way of life economic system food all that jazz I can definately recommend some amazing places to you though Ive taken months and still havent seen nearly everything i wanted to Its a big fing planet From Holst Keith To Andrew Hescock Subject RE duck hook Date Mon Oct Are you in Houston If so I would like to hook up and hear about your trip How many months would you recommend that someone sets aside for a world tour Original Message From Andrew Hescock mailto Sent Thursday October PM To Holst Keith Subject duck hook hey there mr pilot government been around asking you questions about your recent interest in flying hope everything is going well at Enron and with your bird I just got off the phone with a head hunter type lady who is going to try to help me find a trading job in the gaspower industry and I left her you and Toris names as references Just wanted to give you the heads up so you can have enough time to prepare your speech of praise Im sure they wont ask questions about my golf game so you wont have to say anything bad about me Drop me a line sometime and let me know how things are going in htmldiv stylebackgroundcolorDIVHello Mrs Kuykendall hope all is well with you and the babynbsp All done with my trip round the world and got a big boy email account as well now that employers will be looking at it and of course i have to go through the dreaded interviewing process to find gainful employment just spoke with a head hunter lady who is going to help me find a trading job in gaspower and of course i left her your name as one of my many pristine referencesnbsp I left keiths as wellnbsp Hopefully you two are both big swingin dicks in the industry these days and my potential new employers will swoon over your glowing praisenbsp For now though i am trapped at my parents house wasting days doing little other than readingnbsp Its indian summer here in mass today though so im going to get outside before the sun goes downnbsp Read a couple of good books while i was away Rich Man Poor Man by Irwin Shaw and Memoirs of a Geisha w ere both pretty goodnbsp got any recommendations of your ownDIV DIVnbspDIV DIVwrite backDIV DIVdrewDIVdivbr clearallhrGet your FREE download of MSN Explorer at a hrefbqlhmtagitlENaspabrhtml
